aggregate_format.name: Aggregate Format

valid_range.name: Valid Range
valid_range.description: The Valid Range descriptor is an optional characteristic descriptor that defines the minimum and maximum bounds of the characteristic value. If the value as a exponent attached, the exponent also applies to the range values.

presentation_formats.name: Presentation Formats

org.bluetooth.profile.cycling_power.name: Cycling Power
org.bluetooth.profile.cycling_power.description: The Cycling Power Profile is used to enable a data collection device to obtain data from a Cycling Power Sensor (CP Sensor) that exposes the Cycling Power Service .

org.bluetooth.profile.glucose.name: Glucose
org.bluetooth.profile.glucose.description: The Glucose Profile is used to enable a device to obtain glucose measurement and other data from a Glucose Sensor that exposes the Glucose Service.

org.bluetooth.profile.heart_rate.name: Heart Rate
org.bluetooth.profile.heart_rate.description: The Heart Rate Profile is used to enable a data collection device to obtain data from a Heart Rate Sensor that exposes the Heart Rate Service.

org.bluetooth.profile.health_thermometer.name: Health Thermometer
org.bluetooth.profile.health_thermometer.description: The Health Thermometer Profile is used to enable a data collection device to obtain data from a thermometer sensor that exposes the Health Thermometer Service.

org.bluetooth.profile.running_speed_and_.name: Running Speed and Cadence
org.bluetooth.profile.running_speed_and_.description: The Running Speed and Cadence Profile is used to enable a data collection device to obtain data from a Runners Speed and Cadence Sensor (RSC Sensor) that exposes the Speed and Cadence Service.

org.bluetooth.profile.find_me.name: Find Me
org.bluetooth.profile.find_me.description: The Find Me profile defines the behavior when a button is pressed on a device to cause an immediate alert on a peer device. This can be used to allow users to find devices that have been misplaced.

org.bluetooth.profile.phone_alert_status.name: Phone Alert Status
org.bluetooth.profile.phone_alert_status.description: The Phone Alert Status profile is used to obtain the Phone Alert Status exposed by the Phone Alert Status service in the peer device. The information of Alert Status and Ringer Setting of a phone can be received and changed by the Phone Alert Status service. This profile also enables the device to configure ringer status on the peer device.

org.bluetooth.profile.location_and_navig.name: Location and Navigation
org.bluetooth.profile.location_and_navig.description: The Location and Navigation Profile is used to enable a Collector to interact with a Location and Navigation Sensor (LN Sensor) that exposes the Location and Navigation Service for use in outdoor activity applications.

org.bluetooth.profile.alert_notification.name: Alert Notification
org.bluetooth.profile.alert_notification.description: The Alert Notification profile allows a device like a watch to obtain information from a cellphone about incoming calls, missed calls and SMS/MMS messages. The information may include the caller ID for an incoming call or the sender's ID for email/SMS/MMS but not the message. This profile also enables the client device to get information about the number of unread messages on the server device.

org.bluetooth.profile.cycling_speed_and_.name: Cycling Speed and Cadence
org.bluetooth.profile.cycling_speed_and_.description: The Cycling Speed and Cadence Profile is used to enable a data collection device to obtain data from a Cycling Speed and Cadence Sensor (CSC Sensor) that exposes the Cycling Speed and Cadence Service.

org.bluetooth.profile.blood_pressure.name: Blood Pressure
org.bluetooth.profile.blood_pressure.description: The Blood Pressure Profile is used to enable a device to obtain blood pressure measurement and other data from a non-invasive blood pressure sensor that exposes the Blood Pressure Service.

org.bluetooth.profile.scan_parameters.name: Scan Parameters
org.bluetooth.profile.scan_parameters.description: The Scan Parameters Profile is used to provide devices with information to assist them in managing their connection idle timeout and advertising parameters to optimize for power consumption and/or reconnection latency.

sigProfiles.name: org.bluetooth.profile.alert_notification
sigProfiles.description: This profile enables a client device to receive different types of alerts and event information, as well as information on the count of new alerts and unread items, which exist in the server device.

sigProfiles.name: org.bluetooth.profile.blood_pressure
sigProfiles.description: This profile enables a device to connect and interact with a Blood Pressure Sensor device for use in consumer and professional health care applications.

sigProfiles.name: org.bluetooth.profile.cycling_power
sigProfiles.description: This profile enables a Collector device to connect and interact with a Cycling Power Sensor for use in sports and fitness applications.

sigProfiles.name: org.bluetooth.profile.cycling_speed_and_cadence
sigProfiles.description: This profile enables a Collector device to connect and interact with a Cycling Speed and Cadence Sensor for use in sports and fitness applications.

sigProfiles.name: org.bluetooth.profile.find_me
sigProfiles.description: The Find Me profile defines the behavior when a button is pressed on one device to cause an alerting signal on a peer device.

sigProfiles.name: org.bluetooth.profile.glucose
sigProfiles.description: This profile enables a device to connect and interact with a glucose sensor for use in consumer and professional healthcare applications.

sigProfiles.name: org.bluetooth.profile.health_thermometer
sigProfiles.description: This profile enables a Collector device to connect and interact with a Thermometer sensor for use in healthcare applications.

sigProfiles.name: org.bluetooth.profile.heart_rate
sigProfiles.description: This profile enables a Collector device to connect and interact with a Heart Rate Sensor for use in fitness applications.

sigProfiles.name: org.bluetooth.profile.location_and_navigation
sigProfiles.description: This profile enables a Collector device to connect and interact with a Location and Navigation Sensor for use in outdoor activity applications.

sigProfiles.name: org.bluetooth.profile.phone_alert_status
sigProfiles.description: This profile enables a PUID device to alert its user about the alert status of a phone connected to the PUID device.

sigProfiles.name: org.bluetooth.profile.running_speed_and_cadence
sigProfiles.description: This profile enables a Collector device to connect and interact with a Runners Speed and Cadence Sensor for use in sports and fitness applications.

sigProfiles.name: org.bluetooth.profile.scan_parameters
sigProfiles.description: This profile defines how a Scan Client device with Bluetooth low energy wireless communications can write its scanning behavior to a Scan Server, and how a Scan Server can request updates of a Scan Client scanning behavior.

org.bluetooth.service.internet_protocol_.name: Internet Protocol Support Service
org.bluetooth.service.internet_protocol_.description: This service does not define any characteristics

org.bluetooth.service.next_dst_change.description: This service enables a Bluetooth device that has knowledge about the next occurrence of a DST change to expose this information to another Bluetooth device.
org.bluetooth.service.next_dst_change.name: Next DST Change Service

org.bluetooth.service.cycling_speed_and_.description: The Cycling Speed and Cadence (CSC) Service exposes speed-related data and/or cadence-related data while using the Cycling Speed and Cadence sensor (Server).
org.bluetooth.service.cycling_speed_and_.name: Cycling Speed and Cadence

org.bluetooth.service.cycling_power.name: Cycling Power
org.bluetooth.service.cycling_power.description: The Cycling Power (CP) Service exposes power- and force-related data and optionally speed- and cadence-related data from a Cycling Power sensor (Server) intended for sports and fitness applications.

org.bluetooth.service.user_data.name: User Data
org.bluetooth.service.user_data.description: The User Data Service (UDS) exposes user-related data in the sports and fitness environment. This allows remote access and update of user data by a Client as well as the synchronization of user data between a Server and a Client.

org.bluetooth.service.reference_time_upd.description: This service enables a Bluetooth device that can update the system time using reference time such as GPS to expose the control point and the accuracy (drift) of the local system time compared to the reference time source.
org.bluetooth.service.reference_time_upd.name: Reference Time Update Service

org.bluetooth.service.http_proxy.name: HTTP Proxy
org.bluetooth.service.http_proxy.description: The HTTP Proxy Service (HPS) allows a device to expose HTTP Web Services to a client. This enables an HPS client device to program a set of characteristics that configures a Hyper Text Transfer Protocol (HTTP) request, initiate this, request, and then read the response.

org.bluetooth.service.transport_discover.name: Transport Discovery
org.bluetooth.service.transport_discover.description: The Transport Discovery Service (TDS) enables a device using Bluetooth low energy wireless technology to expose services that are available on a transport other than Bluetooth low energy.

org.bluetooth.service.scan_parameters.description: The Scan Parameters Service enables a GATT Server device to expose a characteristic for the GATT Client to write its scan interval and scan window on the GATT Server device.
org.bluetooth.service.scan_parameters.name: Scan Parameters

org.bluetooth.service.link_loss.description: The LINK LOSS Service is instantiated as a Primary Service.    There is only one instance of the Link Loss Service on a device.    There is only one instance of the Alert Level characteristic in a Link Loss Service.    This alert continues until one of following conditions occurs:    An implementation specific timeout    User interaction on this device    A new alert level is written    The physical link is disconnected
org.bluetooth.service.link_loss.name: Link Loss

org.bluetooth.service.alert_notification.description: The Alert Notification service exposes alert information in a device.  This information includes the following: - Type of alert occuring in a device. - Additional text information such as caller ID or sender ID. - Count of new alerts. - Count of unread alert items.
org.bluetooth.service.alert_notification.name: Alert Notification Service

org.bluetooth.service.heart_rate.description: The HEART RATE Service exposes heart rate and other data related to a heart rate sensor intended for fitness applications.
org.bluetooth.service.heart_rate.name: Heart Rate

org.bluetooth.service.generic_access.description: The generic_access service contains generic information about the device. All available Characteristics are readonly.
org.bluetooth.service.generic_access.name: Generic Access

org.bluetooth.service.location_and_navig.name: Location and Navigation
org.bluetooth.service.location_and_navig.description: The Location and Navigation Service (LN Service) exposes location and navigation-related data from a Location and Navigation sensor (Server) intended for outdoor activity applications.

org.bluetooth.service.body_composition.name: Body Composition
org.bluetooth.service.body_composition.description: The Body Composition Service (BCS) exposes data related to body composition from a body composition analyzer (Server) intended for consumer healthcare as well as sports/fitness applications.

org.bluetooth.service.immediate_alert.description: The Immediate Alert service is instantiated as a Primary Service.    There is only one instance of the Immediate Alert service on a device.    There is only one instance of the Alert Level characteristic in an Immediate Alert service.    This alert continues until one of following conditions occurs: - An implementation specific timeout. - User interaction on this device. - A new alert level is written. - The physical link is disconnected.
org.bluetooth.service.immediate_alert.name: Immediate Alert

org.bluetooth.service.tx_power.description: The Tx Power service is instantiated as a Primary Service.    There is only one instance of the Tx Power service on a device.    There is exactly one instance of the Tx Power Level characteristic
org.bluetooth.service.tx_power.name: Tx Power

org.bluetooth.service.battery_service.name: Battery Service
org.bluetooth.service.battery_service.description: The Battery Service exposes the Battery State and Battery Level of a single battery or set of batteries in a device.

org.bluetooth.service.bond_management.description: This service defines how a peer Bluetooth device can manage the storage of bond information, especially the deletion of it, on the Bluetooth device supporting this service.
org.bluetooth.service.bond_management.name: Bond Management Service

org.bluetooth.service.current_time.description: Many Bluetooth devices have the ability to store and show time information. This service defines how a Bluetooth device can expose time information to other Bluetooth devices.
org.bluetooth.service.current_time.name: Current Time Service

org.bluetooth.service.running_speed_and_.name: Running Speed and Cadence
org.bluetooth.service.running_speed_and_.description: The Running Speed and Cadence (RSC) Service exposes speed, cadence and other data related to fitness applications such as the stride length and the total distance the user has traveled while using the Speed and Cadence Sensor (Server).

org.bluetooth.service.weight_scale.description: The Weight Scale (WS) Service exposes weight and related data from a weight scale (Server) intended for consumer healthcare as well as sports/fitness applications.
org.bluetooth.service.weight_scale.name: Weight Scale

org.bluetooth.service.phone_alert_status.description: The Phone Alert Status service uses the Alert Status characteristic, Ringer Setting characteristic to expose the phone alert status and Ringer Control Point characteristic to control phone into mute or enable.
org.bluetooth.service.phone_alert_status.name: Phone Alert Status Service

org.bluetooth.service.health_thermometer.name: Health Thermometer
org.bluetooth.service.health_thermometer.description: The Health Thermometer service is instantiated as a Primary Service.            There are one or more instantiations of the Health Thermometer service per device claiming conformance with this specification.

org.bluetooth.service.device_information.name: Device Information
org.bluetooth.service.device_information.description: This service exposes manufacturer information about a device.    The Device Information Service is instantiated as a Primary Service.    Only one instance of the Device Information Service is exposed on a device.

org.bluetooth.service.continuous_glucose.name: Continuous Glucose Monitoring
org.bluetooth.service.continuous_glucose.description: The Continuous Glucose Monitoring (CGM) Service exposes glucose measurement and other data related to a personal CGM sensor for healthcare applications.

org.bluetooth.service.glucose.description: The Glucose Service exposes glucose and other data related to a glucose sensor for consumer and professional healthcare applications.
org.bluetooth.service.glucose.name: Glucose

org.bluetooth.service.pulse_oximeter.name: Pulse Oximeter Service
org.bluetooth.service.pulse_oximeter.description: The Pulse Oximeter Service exposes pulse oximetry data related to a non-invasive pulse oximetry sensor for consumer and professional healthcare applications.

org.bluetooth.service.blood_pressure.description: The BLOOD PRESSURE Service exposes blood pressure and other data related to a blood pressure monitor.
org.bluetooth.service.blood_pressure.name: Blood Pressure

sigServices.name: org.bluetooth.service.http_proxy
sigServices.description: This service allows a Client device, typically a sensor, to communicate with a Web Server through a gateway device. The gateway device implements the HTTP Proxy Service and therefore provides the services available through the Internet to the Client sensor device.

sigServices.name: org.bluetooth.service.internet_protocol_support
sigServices.description: When in a GAP Discoverable Mode for an initial connection to a Router, the Node will include the IP Support Service UUID 0x1820 in the Service UUIDs AD type field         of the advertising data. This enhances the user experience as a Node may be identified by the Router before initiating a connection.

sigServices.name: org.bluetooth.service.link_loss
sigServices.description: This service defines behavior when a link is lost between two devices.

sigServices.name: org.bluetooth.service.next_dst_change
sigServices.description: This service defines how the information about an upcoming DST change can be exposed using the Generic Attribute Profile (GATT).

sigServices.name: org.bluetooth.service.object_transfer
sigServices.description: This service provides management and control features supporting bulk data transfers which occur via a separate L2CAP connection oriented channel. The Client is enabled to create and delete objects and to execute an action using the currently selected object. The selected object can be written, updated or read via an Object Transfer Channel opened by the Client. The generation of a checksum covering a part or the whole of the object contents is included as an optional feature. This service provides a general method for a Client to select and initiate the transfer of any type of object.

sigServices.name: org.bluetooth.service.pulse_oximeter
sigServices.description: This Service specification proposes a pulse oximetry server for use in consumer and professional healthcare applications.

sigServices.name: org.bluetooth.service.reference_time_update
sigServices.description: This service defines how a client can request an update from a reference time source from a time server using the Generic Attribute Profile (GATT)

sigServices.name: org.bluetooth.service.transport_discovery
sigServices.description: This service enables a device using Bluetooth low energy wireless technology to expose services that are available on a transport other than Bluetooth low energy.         When used together with a higher level specification (e.g., a specification which references and makes use of TDS), the information provided by this service can be         used to facilitate discovery and utilization of BR/EDR or transports not defined by the Bluetooth SIG such as those defined by the Wi-Fi Alliance or other organizations.

sigServices.name: org.bluetooth.service.tx_power
sigServices.description: This service exposes a device's current transmit power level when in a connection.

sigServices.name: org.bluetooth.service.user_data
sigServices.description: This service exposes user-related data in the sports and fitness environment. This allows remote access and update of user data by a Client as well as the synchronization of user data between a Server and a Client.

sigServices.name: org.bluetooth.service.weight_scale
sigServices.description: This service exposes weight and related data from a weight scale intended for consumer healthcare and sports/fitness applications.

sigCharacteristics.description: This characteristic allows the peer device to enable/disable the alert notification of new alert and unread event more selectively than can be done by setting or clearing the notification bit in the Client Characteristic Configuration for each alert characteristic.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.blood_pressure_measurement
sigCharacteristics.description: The BLOOD PRESSURE MEASUREMENT characteristic is used to send a Blood Pressure measurement.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.intermediate_cuff_pressure
sigCharacteristics.description: The INTERMEDIATE CUFF PRESSURE characteristic is used to send intermediate Cuff Pressure values to a device for display purposes while the measurement is in progress.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.blood_pressure_feature
sigCharacteristics.description: The Blood Pressure Feature characteristic is used to describe the supported features of the Blood Pressure Sensor.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.manufacturer_name_string
sigCharacteristics.description: This characteristic represents the name of the manufacturer of the device.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.model_number_string

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.serial_number_string
sigCharacteristics.description: This characteristic represents the serial number for a particular instance of the device.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.hardware_revision_string
sigCharacteristics.description: This characteristic represents the hardware revision for the hardware within the device.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.firmware_revision_string
sigCharacteristics.description: This characteristic represents the firmware revision for the firmware within the device.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.software_revision_string
sigCharacteristics.description: This characteristic represents the software revision for the software within the device.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.system_id
sigCharacteristics.description: This characteristic represents a structure containing an Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI) followed by a manufacturer-defined identifier and is unique for each individual instance of the product.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.ieee_11073-20601_regulatory_certification_data_list
sigCharacteristics.description: This characteristic represents regulatory and certification information for the product in a list defined in IEEE 11073-20601.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.pnp_id
sigCharacteristics.description: The PnP_ID characteristic is a set of values used to create a device ID value that is unique for this device.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.csc_measurement
sigCharacteristics.description: The CSC Measurement characteristic is used to send speed-related data and/or cadence-related data.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.csc_feature
sigCharacteristics.description: The CSC Feature characteristic is used to describe the supported features of the Server. Reserved for Future Use (RFU) bits in the CSC Feature characteristic value are set to 0.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.alert_level
sigCharacteristics.description: The Alert Level characteristic is a control point that allows a peer to command this device to alert to a given level.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.glucose_measurement
sigCharacteristics.description: The Glucose Measurement characteristic is used to send glucose measurements.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.glucose_measurement_context
sigCharacteristics.description: The Glucose Measurement Context characteristic is used to send additional contextual information relative to a Glucose Measurement characteristic.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.glucose_feature
sigCharacteristics.description: The Glucose Feature characteristic is used to describe the supported features of the Server.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.temperature_measurement
sigCharacteristics.description: This characteristic is used to send a temperature measurement.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.temperature_type
sigCharacteristics.description: This characteristic is used to describe the type of temperature measurement in relation to the location on the human body at which the temperature was measured.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.intermediate_temperature
sigCharacteristics.description: This characteristic is used to send intermediate temperature values to a device for display purposes while the measurement is in progress.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.measurement_interval
sigCharacteristics.description: This characteristic is used to enable and control the interval between consecutive temperature measurements.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.heart_rate_measurement
sigCharacteristics.description: This characteristic is used to send a heart rate measurement.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.body_sensor_location
sigCharacteristics.description: The Body Sensor Location characteristic of the device is used to describe the intended location of the heart rate measurement for the device.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.navigation
sigCharacteristics.description: C2: Mandatory if the Navigation feature is supported, otherwise excluded.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.alert_status
sigCharacteristics.description: The Alert Status Characteristic includes three fields of information to express the alerting status as follows.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.ringer_setting
sigCharacteristics.description: The Ringer Setting characteristic returns the current value of the Ringer Setting when read.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.ringer_control_point
sigCharacteristics.description: When the Ringer Control Point characteristic is written, the server device performs an action based on the value (command).

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.rsc_measurement
sigCharacteristics.description: The RSC Measurement characteristic is used to send speed and cadence measurements.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.rsc_feature
sigCharacteristics.description: The RSC Feature characteristic is used to describe the supported features of the Server. Reserved for Future Use (RFU) bits in the SC Feature characteristic value are set to 0.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.scan_interval_window
sigCharacteristics.description: The Scan Interval Window characteristic is used to store the scan parameters of the Client. Included in this characteristic are the Scan Interval and Scan Window of the Client.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.scan_refresh
sigCharacteristics.description: The Scan Refresh characteristic is used to notify the Client that the Server requires the Scan Interval Window characteristic to be written with the latest values upon notification.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.battery_level
sigCharacteristics.description: The Battery Level characteristic is read using the GATT Read Characteristic Value sub-procedure and returns the current battery level as a percentage from 0% to 100%;                 0% represents a battery that is fully discharged, 100% represents a battery that is fully charged.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.object_list_control_point
sigCharacteristics.description: C1:Mandatory if the Server is capable of storing more than one object within the context of this instance of the service; optional otherwise.

sigCharacteristics.name: org.bluetooth.characteristic.object_list_filter
